
[1]substitution

   SUBSTITU'TION, n. The act of putting one person or thing in the place
   of another to supply its place; as the substitution of an agent,
   attorney or representative to act for one in his absence; the
   substitution of bank notes for gold and silver, as a circulating
   medium.

   1. In grammar, syllepsis, or the use of one word for another.
